<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-08-05T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-08-05T14:00:00-05:00" n="144" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d144">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">835.6363/444: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Cox</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos
                                        Aires</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-08-05T15:00:00-04:00">August 5, 1936—3
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 5:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>155. Embassy’s 150, July 29, 10 a.m. Embassy is informed that the private
                            oil companies have applied for enrollment on register <pb facs="0288" n="189" xml:id="pg_189"/> mentioned in article 4 of executive decree
                            and are now waiting to see what action YPF takes regarding their
                            importation requests.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Cox</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>